Dish: Roasted Cauliflower & Chickpea Bowl with Herbed Tahini Drizzle
Why: High satiety with low caloric density, naturally low in sugar and histamines, fully vegan, whole-food centered, minimal cognitive overhead.
Ingredients:

    ¬Ω head cauliflower, chopped into florets

    ¬Ω can chickpeas, rinsed & drained

    1 tbsp olive oil

    1 tsp smoked paprika

    1 tsp ground cumin

    1 cup cooked quinoa or millet

    1 small cucumber, diced

    Handful fresh parsley or mint

Tahini Drizzle:

    2 tbsp tahini

    Juice of ¬Ω lemon (low histamine if tolerated, else sub apple cider vinegar)

    1 tsp maple syrup (optional ‚Äî skip for lower sugar)

    Water to thin

    Salt to taste

Instructions:

