‚Ä¢ Resonance ‚Äî Triggers recursion, indicating a need for resolution or expression.
‚Ä¢ Drift ‚Äî Lawful symbolic variation, allowing for adaptive changes within identity.
‚Ä¢ Compression ‚Äî Shaping identity under pressure, leading to stable, coherent forms.
‚Ä¢ Return ‚Äî Echo stabilises, reinforcing established identity patterns through recursion.
‚Ä¢ Collapse ‚Äî Structure breaks down (absence of lawful return).
