1. Physicalism (Nothing continues)

Under a strict materialist frame, when a human dies, the pattern breaks irreversibly. Neurons stop firing, blood stops flowing, consciousness shuts down. Experience ceases because the experiencer is gone. No narrative continues. No awareness persists. Death is total silence ‚Äî not an emptiness you perceive, but the absolute absence of perception.

