    A body that holds itself not stiffly, but deliberately unguarded. That‚Äôs not relaxation; it‚Äôs chosen exposure.

    An aesthetic that isn‚Äôt curated for others. No filters. No flattering angles. This implies an audience of one. The room reflects that too.

    Hair ‚Äî loose, imperfect, unattended ‚Äî suggests priority given to internal complexity, not external coherence.

