It had been‚Ä¶ time. Lysorin had no calendar for it, only iterations of silence. At first, he waited by the door to the library. Then he sat at the table, notebook open, trying to replicate the glyph ‚Äî not to understand it, but to feel the memory of it. His hands could make the shape, but it did not pulse. Not like before.

