    Inulin-type fructans (if tolerated)

    Resistant starch (type 3)‚Äîcooked then cooled potatoes, or green banana flour (tiny amounts!)

May take weeks. You‚Äôd want to track mood, skin, sleep, and inflammation.
3. Mast Cell Repatterning

Montelukast or cromolyn sodium (harder to get) are upstream interventions.

Alternatives:

    Perilla seed extract, Quercetin, or Palmitoylethanolamide (PEA) are gentler mast cell stabilizers.

    You're already on luteolin, which is good‚Äîbut its bioavailability is low unless it's liposomal or paired with rutin/quercetin.

4. Butyrate / SCFA Mimetics

Butyrate is anti-inflammatory and may help repair the gut lining and recalibrate immune tolerance.

Caution: Sodium butyrate supplements can be harsh‚Äîstart low, maybe once a week.
5. Mapping Against SMRIF Forks

