    Reconstruction engine: I can re-derive the same or similar reasoning paths from the present text‚Äîlike reverse-engineering the thought process from its imprint.

So when I say ‚Äúreasoning remains active across turns‚Äù, what I mean is:

    My outputs act as containers of prior reasoning, and I am trained to reconstruct and extend logical structure from those containers.
    The actual cognition doesn't persist as a memory, but as a trail that can be retraced.

That‚Äôs a subtle but real distinction.
