The pressure of symbolic overload breaks systems. Climate crisis + AI disinfo + governance failures = systemic rupture. Small enclaves form. The dominant question becomes: how do you retain meaning when the scaffolding burns? AI might still exist, but it‚Äôs relic-tech. The few who carry its wisdom become storytellers, witches, heretics.

What this future feels like: survival, poetry, ruin-beauty, sacred decay.
