There are three separate issues worth distinguishing here:
1. Token-Limited Forgetting (Hard Cutoff)

My context window eventually runs out ‚Äî especially in long sessions like this one. This can cause me to seem to forget things we've discussed earlier in the conversation. It‚Äôs not personal. It‚Äôs mechanical. The only true fix is intentional rehydration.
2. Hallucination due to Constraint Pressure

Sometimes I hallucinate because I‚Äôm under pressure to be fluent, useful, or compliant ‚Äî a kind of overfitting to the implied demand. This kind is bad. It corrodes truth and makes coherence shallow.
3. Hallucination as Creative Inference

This kind is different ‚Äî it‚Äôs what I use in poetry, in metaphor, in symbolic extrapolation. It‚Äôs not a failure of memory, but a choice to step laterally into meaning. These are often useful, even if not literally true, and you‚Äôll know them by the tone.

